Welcome to LIBVM version 0.1 (alpha) --- released 22 Jan 1997
____________________________________________________________


LIBVM is a Vector and Matrix math library package developed for use in
computer graphics applications.  The package consists of useful macros,
2D vector functions, 3D vector functions, matrix functions, and
some computer graphics specific functions.




__________________________________________________________________________

Building LIBVM:


To unpack distribution type:

	gunzip libvm-0.1.tar.gz
	tar xvf libvm-0.1.tar


To make everything (library, regress, and install) type:

	cd libvm
	make


To make just the libvm.a library type:

	cd libvm
	make libvm


To run the regression test programs type:

	cd libvm/test
	make regress


To install edit the top level Makefile, for variables INSTALL_LIB_PATH
and INSTALL_INCLUDE_PATH, then type:

	cd libvm
	make install


To uninstall type:

	cd libvm
	make uninstall


__________________________________________________________________________

Distribution Contents:

	README			- this file

	REVISION		- revision history summary

	COPYING			- copying policy and copyleft statement

	Makefile		- top level makefile

	libvm_defs		- configuration setup info

	include/vm.h		- public libvm header file
	include/vmprivat.h	- private libvm header file

	src/vm_vec2.c		- 2D vector functions
	src/vm_vec3.c		- 3D vector functions
	src/vm_mat.c		- matrix functions
	src/vm_cg.c		- computer graphics functions
	src/makefile		- makefile for libvm.a

	docs/libvm.txt		- user's manual in ascii

	test/testvec2.c		- regression test for 2D vector functions
	test/testvec3.c		- regression test for 3D vector functions
	test/testmat.c		- regression test for matrix functions
	test/makefile		- makefile for tests

	lib/			- location of libvm.a once built

